item.title: Urge SEC to take action against Gadwal MLA for violations: BRS
item.description:
<![CDATA[
Hyderabad: The Bharat Rashtra Samithi (BRS) has urged the Telangana State Election Commission (TGSEC) to take action against Gadwal MLA Bandla Krishna Mohan Reddy, alleging that he campaigned during the prohibited 48-hour silence period and held meetings and voter interactions after the campaign deadline. The BRS leaders also accused him of misusing his political position and influence to sway voters and creating an atmosphere of pressure and inducement among the electorate.BRS leaders Kuruv...]]>
